{
  "stem": "3382.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And of course, these Jewish children had a negative attitude towards me.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Because here came a Russian aristocrat, they said to me.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "All right.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was at the time 11, 12.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And like now, I realize no, so that somehow that I rolled down-- you know, the feeling that I rolled down from a big, high peak to a deep ravine.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And also, for the first time, I saw, you know, unpaved streets, you know, children running barefoot in whatever you may call clothes.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But it was not clothes, you know?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was-- psychologically, it was just a big-- very unpleasant.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SIGHS] So--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then I went to a Russian high school.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But in, in the next year, that Russian high school turned into Polish.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "By the way, I lost one year.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because when they gave me the exam from Polish-- so I wrote such tremendously stupid things that [LAUGHS] I don't believe how I could-- I-- [LAUGHS] when I look back.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It is very hard to translate it into English.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But I, I wrote idiotic dictate.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So they put me back one year.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I lost one year.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It's why I graduated-- instead of 18-- '28, when I was-- you know, I graduated when I was 19.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the first three years was very, very hard for me on account of language.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And then I never picked up a good Polish language.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Because surrounding, I had that local eastern Polish language, which differs strongly from literal Polish, first of all, in pronunciation and some other things.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But I became a kind of expert in this language and later even wrote some short stories about it after the war.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You know, when I was in the fifth grade or so, my stepfather-- we didn't go along.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
